This paper deals with wireless sensor network protocols and their information dissemination, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper specifically focuses on the Trickle algorithm, which is commonly used in low-power and lossy networks, and proposes a heuristic algorithm to improve its performance. This involves analyzing the redundancy constants used in Trickle, which could also fall under the categories of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), systems and control (cs.SY), information theory (cs.IT), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). However, given the emphasis on wireless sensor networks and networked systems, cs.NI is the most likely category.
